[debug] [2026-03-13T18:33:01.216Z] <<< [apiv2][status] POST https://cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com/v1beta/projects/sadak-saathi/locations/global/instances/default:completeTask 200
[debug] [2026-03-13T18:33:01.216Z] <<< [apiv2][body] POST https://cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com/v1beta/projects/sadak-saathi/locations/global/instances/default:completeTask {"output":{"messages":[{"content":"Here are four operations for your app, based on the provided schema and best practices for Firebase Data Connect, including proper authentication and `insecureReason` where applicable.\n\n```graphql\nquery ListAllUsers @auth(level: USER, insecureReason: \"This operation is safe to expose to all logged in users.\") {\n  users {\n    username\n    email\n    avatarUrl\n    bio\n  }\n}\n\nmutation CreateNewUser($username: String!, $email: String!) @auth(level: USER) {\n  user_insert(data: {\n    username: $username,\n    email: $email,\n    createdAt_expr: \"request.time\"\n  }) {\n    uid\n  }\n}\n\nmutation UpdateMyUserBio($bio: String!) @auth(level: USER) {\n  user_update(key: {uid_expr: \"auth.uid\"}, data: {\n    bio: $bio\n  }) {\n    uid\n  }\n}\n\nquery GetMyUser @auth(level: USER) {\n  users(where: {uid: {eq_expr: \"auth.uid\"}}) {\n    username\n    email\n    avatarUrl\n    bio\n    createdAt\n  }\n}\n```\n\nLet's break down these operations:\n\n1.  **`ListAllUsers`**: This query allows any logged-in user to see a list of all other users and their public profile information.\n2.  **`CreateNewUser`**: This mutation allows a new user to register by providing their username and email. The `createdAt` field is automatically populated on the server.\n3.  **`UpdateMyUserBio`**: This mutation allows a logged-in user to update their own biographical information. Notice how `uid_expr: \"auth.uid\"` is used to ensure only the authenticated user can modify their own record.\n4.  **`GetMyUser`**: This query allows a logged-in user to retrieve their own profile details. Similar to the update, `uid_expr: \"auth.uid\"` ensures the user can only fetch their own data.\n\nHere are a few follow-up questions you might consider:\n\n*   How would I implement a query to search for users by their username?\n*   What would a mutation look like to delete a user's account?\n*   How can I add more granular access control, for example, only allowing administrators to see certain user fields?","author":"model"}]},"outputDataContext":{"additionalContext":{"@type":"type.googleapis.com/google.cloud.cloudaicompanion.v1main.ChatOutputDataContext","relatedContent":{}}},"attributionContext":{"citationMetadata":{}}}
